<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="218" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,476,719]" box="[151,1275,512,539]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,512,539]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Distribution:</emphasis>
South-west Europe, North Africa, 
<collectingCountry box="[698,782,513,539]" name="Cyprus" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
, and the Near East (
<bibRefCitation author="Astafurova, Y. V. &amp; Proshchalykin, M. Y. &amp; Schwarz, M." box="[1005,1263,512,539]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" pagination="13 - 40" refId="ref20226" refString="Astafurova, Y. V., Proshchalykin, M. Y. &amp; Schwarz, M. (2019) The distribution of the genus Sphecodes Latreille (Hymenoptera, Halictidae) of the Arabian Peninsula and surrounding countries with description of hitherto unknown female of S. atlanticus Warncke, 1992 and male of S. dathei Schwarz, 2010. Zookeys, 872, 13 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 872.35361" type="journal article" year="2019">
Astafurova 
<emphasis box="[1139,1188,512,538]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,476,719]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,227,549,575]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Notes:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke, K." box="[235,416,548,575]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" pagination="31 - 77" refId="ref23322" refString="Warncke, K. (1992) Die westpalaarktischen Arten der Bienengattung Coelioxys Latr. (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Megachilidae). Bericht der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft Augsburg, 53, 31 - 77." type="journal article" year="1992">Warncke (1992)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1839" box="[552,675,548,575]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubripes">
<emphasis box="[552,675,548,575]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">S. rubripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius, 1793)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[923,1361,548,575]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albilabris">
<emphasis box="[923,1158,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Sphecodes albilabris</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1793)
</taxonomicName>
. However, it has several morphological and ecological differences (
<bibRefCitation author="Bogusch, P. &amp; Straka, J." box="[888,1162,584,611]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" pagination="1 - 41" refId="ref20454" refString="Bogusch, P. &amp; Straka, J. (2012) Review and identification of the cuckoo bees of central Europe (Hymenoptera: Halictidae: Sphecodes). Zootaxa, 3311 (1), 1 - 41. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3311.1.1" type="journal article" year="2012">Bogusch &amp; Straka 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cross, I." box="[1172,1302,585,611]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" pagination="12 - 14" refId="ref20701" refString="Cross, I. (2017) Eucera nigrilabris Lepeletier, 1841 is the host of Sphecodes rubripes Spinola, 1838 Hymenoptera: Aculeata). Ampulex, 9, 12 - 14." type="journal article" year="2017">Cross 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Astafurova, Y. V. &amp; Proshchalykin, M. Y. &amp; Schwarz, M." pageId="17" pageNumber="218" pagination="13 - 40" refId="ref20226" refString="Astafurova, Y. V., Proshchalykin, M. Y. &amp; Schwarz, M. (2019) The distribution of the genus Sphecodes Latreille (Hymenoptera, Halictidae) of the Arabian Peninsula and surrounding countries with description of hitherto unknown female of S. atlanticus Warncke, 1992 and male of S. dathei Schwarz, 2010. Zookeys, 872, 13 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 872.35361" type="journal article" year="2019">
Astafurova 
<emphasis box="[198,250,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
) and should be considered a valid species (
<bibRefCitation author="Bogusch, P. &amp; Straka, J." box="[831,1115,620,647]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" pagination="47982116" refId="ref20507" refString="Bogusch, P. &amp; Straka, J. (2014) Sphecodes rubripes. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species, 2014, e. T 47982116 A 47996274. https: // doi. org / 10.2305 / IUCN. UK. 2014 - 2. RLTS. T 47982116 A 47996274. en" type="journal article" year="2014">Bogusch &amp; Straka 2014</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[1170,1268,620,646]" name="Portugal" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1839" box="[1282,1408,620,647]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubripes">
<emphasis box="[1282,1408,620,647]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">S. rubripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the Algarve where it is a parasite of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lepeletier, 1841" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[789,1182,656,683]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Eucera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrilabris">
<emphasis box="[789,996,656,682]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Eucera nigrilabris</emphasis>
Lepeletier, 1841
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cross, I." box="[1195,1327,657,683]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" pagination="12 - 14" refId="ref20701" refString="Cross, I. (2017) Eucera nigrilabris Lepeletier, 1841 is the host of Sphecodes rubripes Spinola, 1838 Hymenoptera: Aculeata). Ampulex, 9, 12 - 14." type="journal article" year="2017">Cross 2017</bibRefCitation>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[198,335,692,719]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albilabris">
<emphasis box="[198,335,692,719]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">S. albilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[342,481,692,719]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
is found throughout the country.
</paragraph>
